1 0 0 1 56 736.0 Tm (that the Roman material sets slowly and is initially weaker than modern concrete, an) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 722.0 Tm (unacceptable trade-off for structures that must bear load immediately. Its virtues emerge) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 708.0 Tm (only over centuries, a timescale beyond ordinary engineering practice.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 694.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 680.0 Tm (Part of the answer is also that the specific volcanic ash the Romans used is not uniformly) Tj
